scrubber
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:an ill-thrifty cow or ewe, i.e. one of poor quality and production, originally grazing in scrub.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
